When Jerry & I married he gave me 29 white roses-Turkowar filly's name was in honor of that. Irgun filly was named Catgotyirgun. #KyDerby
But Turkancer was victim of selenium poisoning via bad hay & unable to breed so we went w Turkowar. We named the filly TwentyNine Roses...
Turkancer's 1st several foals all raced & won, & a friend bought him to stand at MO farm, along w his son. We wanted to breed Mystic to him.
Turkancer was gorgeous black who never raced due to injury but became very successful upper level dressage horse who sired a few foals...
In my landscape pic, Mystic Cat is w 2008 filly by Turkowar, by Turkancer, by Turkoman. Interesting story there: Turkowar was OH Horse of Yr
Mystic's grandsires were Storm Cat & Majestic Light, whose sires were Secretariat & Majestic Prince, both #KentuckyDerby winers.
Irgun, sired by Derby winner Sunny's Halo, Secretariat & Halo as grandsires. Our mare, Mystic Cat, was by Mountain Cat, 1st 2yo to win $2mil
Irgun was unbeaten fave for 94 Derby but was injured wk b4. Vid above shows him beating eventual Derby winner Go For Gin in Wood Memorial.
